      "name": "Construct stiffness QoI comparison — FEA vs. experiment",
      "description": "FEA-predicted construct stiffness (N/mm) compared against N=11 experimental measurements pooled across two independent laboratories. Mean experimental stiffness 312.4 N/mm (SD 18.7); FEA ensemble mean 304.1 N/mm. Percent difference 2.7%, well within the pre-established 10% acceptance bound. Validation metric E/uval = 0.83, below the 1.96 threshold. This result was generated during the formal validation campaign conducted at FDA CDRH and DePuy Synthes facilities between January and March 2023, using the Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 solver with verified mesh density (mesh convergence study documented in report NGA-MC-2023-01). Boundary conditions replicated ASTM F1717 fixture geometry to within 0.05 mm tolerance; material properties drawn from certified coupon testing of Ti-6Al-4V rod stock (lot 2022-DPS-447). The detailed simulation log, solver output files, and post-processing scripts are archived in the project repository under tag v1.3.2-validation.",
